-- RBC Hires
-- B y   M a r k   S h e n k
-- 2013-07-09T14:42:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-09/rbc-hires.html
RBC Capital Markets hired William
Argiriou and J. Chris McCormack as co-heads of its energy
futures desk in New York.  Argiriou will be responsible for client coverage of energy
producers, refiners, banks and hedge funds. He comes from UBS,
where he was head of New York commodities.  McCormack’s focus will be large-cap oil companies, banks,
trading companies and hedge funds. McCormack also comes from
UBS, where he was an executive director in exchange-traded
derivatives.  Argiriou and McCormack will report to Eric Aldous, the head
of clearing services and futures at RBC in New York.  RBC Capital Markets is the investment-banking unit of the
 Royal Bank of Canada . The Montreal-based lender is the country’s
largest bank.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mark Shenk in New York at 
